description:
This Summer, meet the residents of Element City

Watch the new trailer for Disney and Pixar‚Äôs #Elemental and see the movie in 3D, only in theaters June 16!

Check out a brand-new trailer for Disney and Pixar‚Äôs ‚ÄúElemental,‚Äù an all-new original feature film that transports moviegoers to an extraordinary place called Element City, where a host of elements live and work. The trailer showcases each element‚Äîair, earth, water and fire‚Äîand what sets them apart according to Ember, a quick-witted and fiery woman who‚Äôs always stayed close to home in Firetown. In ‚ÄúElemental,‚Äù which opens in theaters on June 16, she finally ventures out of her comfort zone to explore this spectacular world born from the imaginations of Pixar‚Äôs filmmakers and specifically crafted for the big-screen experience. Element City is inspired by big cities around the globe and embraces theorized contributions from each elemental community‚Äîfrom giant pine-tree-like buildings and waterfall skyscrapers to a tornado-shaped arena called Cyclone Stadium. 

Joining the previously announced voice cast including Leah Lewis and Mamoudou Athie as Ember and Wade, respectively, are Ronnie del Carmen as Ember‚Äôs soon-to-be retired dad, Bernie; Shila Ommi as Ember‚Äôs love-seeking mom, Cinder; Wendi McLendon-Covey as Wade‚Äôs stormy and Air-Ball-loving boss, Gale; Catherine O‚ÄôHara as Wade‚Äôs welcoming mom, Brook; Mason Wertheimer as Ember‚Äôs admiring earth neighbor, Clod; and Joe Pera as an overgrown city bureaucrat, Fern.
 
Directed by Peter Sohn, produced by Denise Ream, p.g.a., and executive produced by Pete Docter, ‚ÄúElemental‚Äù features a screenplay by John Hoberg & Kat Likkel and Brenda Hsueh with story by Sohn, Hoberg & Likkel and Hsueh. title: TROLLS BAND TOGETHER | Official Trailer
description:
Trolls Band Together - In Theaters this Fall

This holiday season, get ready for an action-packed, all-star, rainbow-colored family reunion like no other as Anna Kendrick and Justin Timberlake return for the new chapter in DreamWorks Animation‚Äôs blockbuster musical franchise: Trolls Band Together. 

After two films of true friendship and relentless flirting, Poppy (Anna Kendrick) and Branch (Justin Timberlake) are now officially, finally, a couple (#broppy)! As they grow closer, Poppy discovers that Branch has a secret past. He was once part of her favorite boyband phenomenon, BroZone, with his four brothers: Floyd (Golden Globe nominated electropop sensation Troye Sivan), John Dory (Eric Andr√©; Sing 2), Spruce (Grammy winner Daveed Diggs; Hamilton) and Clay (Grammy winner Kid Cudi; Don‚Äôt Look Up). BroZone disbanded when Branch was still a baby, as did the family, and Branch hasn‚Äôt seen his brothers since.  

But when Branch‚Äôs bro Floyd is kidnapped for his musical talents by a pair of nefarious pop-star villains‚ÄîVelvet (Emmy winner Amy Schumer; Trainwreck) and Veneer (Grammy winner and Tony nominee Andrew Rannells; The Book of Mormon)‚ÄîBranch and Poppy embark on a harrowing and emotional journey to reunite the other brothers and rescue Floyd from a fate even worse than pop-culture obscurity. 

Featuring Trolls‚Äô signature psychedelic joy-bomb of new and classic pop hits, Trolls Band Together stars a dazzling cast of musical superstars and comedic powerhouses as new franchise characters, including four-time Grammy nominee and Latin Grammy winner Camila Cabello (Cinderella) as Viva; Zosia Mamet (The Flight Attendant) as Crimp; and 12-time Emmy winning drag icon RuPaul Charles as Miss Maxine. 

The returning cast includes Grammy, Emmy and Golden Globe nominee Zooey Deschanel as Bridget; Christopher Mintz-Plasse as Gristle, the Icona Pop duo Aino Jawo and Caroline Hjelt as Satin and Chenille, Grammy winner Anderson .Paak as Prince D, comedian Ron Funches as Cooper, SAG nominee Kunal Nayyar as Guy Diamond and Emmy winning Saturday Night Live legend Kenan Thompson as Tiny Diamond. 

Trolls Band Together is steered by returning director Walt Dohrn and producer Gina Shay, and is co-directed by Tim Heitz (head of story, Trolls World Tour). DreamWorks Animation‚Äôs Trolls films‚Äî2016‚Äôs Trolls and 2020‚Äôs Trolls World Tour‚Äîhave sung and danced their way to record-breaking success, earning an Oscar¬Æ nomination for Best Original Song and fueling one of the largest and most beloved entertainment brands in the world.

‚ÄúThe Little Mermaid‚Äù is the beloved story of Ariel,¬†a beautiful and spirited young mermaid with a thirst for adventure. The youngest of King Triton‚Äôs daughters and the most defiant, Ariel longs to find out more about the world beyond the sea and, while visiting the surface, falls for the dashing Prince Eric.¬†While mermaids are forbidden to interact with humans, Ariel must follow her heart. She makes a deal with the evil sea witch, Ursula, which gives her a chance to experience life on land but ultimately places her life ‚Äì and her father‚Äôs crown ‚Äì in jeopardy. ‚ÄúThe Little Mermaid‚Äù is directed by Oscar¬Æ nominee Rob Marshall (‚ÄúChicago,‚Äù ‚ÄúMary Poppins Returns‚Äù) with a screenplay by two-time Oscar nominee David Magee (‚ÄúLife of Pi,‚Äù ‚ÄúFinding Neverland‚Äù). title: Escape The Mothball Fleet
description:
Explore rarely-exposed areas of a World War II battleship as you gather the intel needed to‚Ä¶

Escape The Mothball Fleet

Get ready for a thrilling, once-in-a-lifetime adventure that blends elements of an escape room and a scavenger hunt to challenge you in a whole new way.

Unravel enigmatic clues, follow mysterious markings, and search off-limits areas as you race against the clock to save the largest battleship in United States history.

This adventure-game was inspired by real-life events. The challenge awaiting you was lived by our team, as they scrambled to meet a shockingly-short window of opportunity. If they had failed, USS IOWA might have been doomed to the scrapheap of history.

Now you have the chance to retrace their steps ‚Äì exploring a vessel you‚Äôve never been aboard and under pressure to find the answers you need before time runs out.

Your experience starts with a briefing, then you begin your adventure, hunting for clues through the seemingly endless maze of hundreds of ship compartments, companionways, and ladders.  You have two hours to complete your tasks, otherwise IOWA might be lost forever.

Don‚Äôt worry. You‚Äôll have members of our trained ship support staff with you, but don‚Äôt count on them to help. They‚Äôre only along for your safety (and it takes them weeks to learn the ship) ‚Äì you‚Äôll be navigating on your own!

You and your favorite group of family or friends will remember this experience for a lifetime!

title: The Little Mermaid | The Cast Goes Under The Sea
description:
ü§©THIS CASTü§© Go behind-the-scenes of #TheLittleMermaid to see how this cast became a family!

‚ÄúThe Little Mermaid,‚Äù visionary filmmaker Rob Marshall‚Äôs live-action reimagining of the studio‚Äôs Oscar¬Æ-winning animated musical classic, opens exclusively in theaters nationwide May 26, 2023. ‚ÄúThe Little Mermaid‚Äù is the beloved story of Ariel, a beautiful and spirited young mermaid with a thirst for adventure. The youngest of King Triton‚Äôs daughters, and the most defiant, Ariel longs to find out more about the world beyond the sea, and while visiting the surface, falls for the dashing Prince Eric. While mermaids are forbidden to interact with humans, Ariel must follow her heart. She makes a deal with the evil sea witch, Ursula, which gives her a chance to experience life on land, but ultimately places her life ‚Äì and her father‚Äôs crown ‚Äì in jeopardy. 

The film stars singer and actress Halle Bailey (‚Äúgrown-ish‚Äù) as Ariel; Tony Award¬Æ winner Daveed Diggs (‚ÄúHamilton,‚Äù ‚ÄúSnowpiercer‚Äù) as the voice of Sebastian; Jacob Tremblay (‚ÄúLuca,‚Äù ‚ÄúRoom‚Äù) as the voice of Flounder; Awkwafina (‚ÄúRaya and the Last Dragon‚Äù) as the voice of Scuttle; Jonah Hauer-King (‚ÄúA Dog‚Äôs Way Home‚Äù) as Prince Eric; Art Malik (‚ÄúHomeland‚Äù) as Sir Grimsby; Noma Dumezweni (‚ÄúMary Poppins Returns‚Äù) as Queen Selina; with Oscar¬Æ winner Javier Bardem (‚ÄúNo Country for Old Men,‚Äù ‚ÄúBeing the Ricardos‚Äù) as King Triton; and two-time Academy Award¬Æ nominee Melissa McCarthy (‚ÄúCan You Ever Forgive Me?‚Äù ‚ÄúBridesmaids‚Äù) as Ursula.      

‚ÄúThe Little Mermaid‚Äù is directed by Oscar¬Æ nominee Rob Marshall (‚ÄúChicago,‚Äù ‚ÄúMary Poppins Returns‚Äù), and written by two-time Oscar nominee David Magee (‚ÄúLife of Pi,‚Äù ‚ÄúFinding Neverland‚Äù), with a live-action story adaptation by David Magee, Rob Marshall, and two-time Emmy winner John DeLuca (‚ÄúTony Bennett: An American Classic‚Äù), based on the short story by Hans Christian Andersen, and the Disney animated film by Ron Clements and John Musker. The film is produced by two-time Emmy¬Æ winner Marc Platt (‚ÄúJesus Christ Superstar Live in Concert,‚Äù ‚ÄúGrease Live!‚Äù), three-time Tony Award¬Æ winner Lin-Manuel Miranda (‚ÄúHamilton,‚Äù ‚ÄúIn the Heights‚Äù), Rob Marshall, and John DeLuca, with Jeffrey Silver (‚ÄúThe Lion King‚Äù) serving as executive producer. The score is by multiple Academy Award¬Æ winner Alan Menken (‚ÄúBeauty and the Beast,‚Äù ‚ÄúAladdin‚Äù), who won two Oscars¬Æ for the music in the animated version of ‚ÄúThe Little Mermaid,‚Äù with music supervised and produced by Mike Higham (‚ÄúMary Poppins Returns,‚Äù ‚ÄúInto the Woods‚Äù). Music is by Alan Menken, lyrics are by Howard Ashman and new lyrics are by Lin-Manuel Miranda.

title: The Mystery of Human DNA (Science Uprising EP3)
description:
Is the software that runs life the result of accumulated copying errors? Or does it require a programmer? This episode of Science Uprising examines how Microsoft founder Bill Gates, geneticist and entrepreneur Craig Venter, and even evolutionary biologist Richard Dawkins all acknowledge that DNA is like software. But how was that software created?

Be sure to visit https://scienceuprising.com/ to find more videos and explore related articles and books.

People featured in this episode include Stephen Meyer, PhD, Director of the Center for Science and Culture at Discovery Institute and author of Signature in the Cell: DNA and the Evidence for Intelligent Design; and Douglas Axe, Maxwell Visiting Professor of Molecular Biology at Biola University and author of Undeniable: How Biology Confirms Our Intuition that Life Is Designed.

============================

Science Uprising

Well-known scientists have been preaching a materialistic worldview rather than presenting the public with all the evidence. We are here to change that. The objective scientific evidence does not prove our universe is blind and purposeless.  It does not show we are simply meat machines. It does not prove that evolutionary mechanisms can completely account for the diversity of life on earth. This is what THEY want you to think. Think for yourself and make an informed decision.
Are you ready? The uprising has begun.

Visit the Science Uprising website at https://scienceuprising.com/ to find more videos and explore related articles and books. You can also find out more information about the people interviewed in this episode.

description:
Oris and Disney‚Äôs The Muppets Kermit the Frog get together for a bit of fun and to create ‚ÄúKermit Day‚Äù with a very special edition of the ProPilot X Calibre 400.

We‚Äôre inspired by what we call the Joy of Mechanics. The first function of every Oris watch, in the purest emotional, feel-it-in-yourbones sense, is to bring joy, to make people smile. That‚Äôs it. If an Oris watch can make someone‚Äôs day better, we‚Äôve done our job.

For some time, we‚Äôve been trying to find the ultimate expression of this and to make a watch that‚Äôs pure joy. And then it hit us. A collaboration with the easiest guy on the planet: Kermit the Frog from The Muppet Show. Kermit‚Äôs role is to entertain, to put a smile on our faces. He‚Äôs been doing it for generations. Could we do a watch with him?

It turns out we could. And we‚Äôre delighted, grinning from ear to ear, and so proud to introduce you to the ProPilot X Kermit Edition.

It‚Äôs based on our 39mm titanium ProPilot X Calibre 400, only it‚Äôs got a green dial ‚Äì and a twist. On the first of every month, the date window at 6 o‚Äôclock will be filled with a Kermit the Frog emoji. ‚ÄúKermit Day‚Äù is all about not taking life too seriously. Having some fun. title: GRAND FESTIVAL FINALE @ 9th Mallorca Smooth Jazz Festival 2022
description:
On November 6, 2022 at 10:15 pm, the GRAND FESTIVAL FINALE concert took place in Sa Coma, a coastal town on the Spanish island of Mallorca. The event marked the end of the 9th Mallorca Smooth Jazz Festival. Many musicians of the week-long festival took part in this unique event. This video shows the full concert.

title: The Little Mermaid | In Theaters May 26
description:
Watch and you'll see, some day I'll be, part of your world! See the movie #TheLittleMermaid in theaters May 26!

The brand new soundtrack for Disney‚Äôs ‚ÄúThe Little Mermaid‚Äù is available now to Pre-Save, Pre-Add or Pre-Order ‚Äì¬†https://presave.umusic.com/thelittlemermaidsoundtrack

‚ÄúThe Little Mermaid‚Äù is the beloved story of Ariel,¬†a beautiful and spirited young mermaid with a thirst for adventure. The youngest of King Triton‚Äôs daughters and the most defiant, Ariel longs to find out more about the world beyond the sea and, while visiting the surface, falls for the dashing Prince Eric.¬†While mermaids are forbidden to interact with humans, Ariel must follow her heart. She makes a deal with the evil sea witch, Ursula, which gives her a chance to experience life on land but ultimately places her life ‚Äì and her father‚Äôs crown ‚Äì in jeopardy. The film stars singer and¬†actress Halle Bailey (‚Äúgrown-ish‚Äù) as Ariel; Jonah Hauer-King (‚ÄúA Dog‚Äôs Way Home‚Äù) as Prince Eric; Tony Award¬Æ winner Daveed Diggs (‚ÄúHamilton‚Äù) as the voice of Sebastian; Awkwafina (‚ÄúRaya and the Last Dragon‚Äù) as the voice of Scuttle; Jacob Tremblay (‚ÄúLuca‚Äù) as the voice of Flounder; Noma Dumezweni (‚ÄúMary Poppins Returns‚Äù) as Queen Selina; Art Malik (‚ÄúHomeland‚Äù) as Sir Grimsby; with Oscar¬Æ winner Javier Bardem (‚ÄúNo Country for Old Men‚Äù) as King Triton; and two-time Academy Award¬Æ nominee Melissa McCarthy (‚ÄúCan You Ever Forgive Me?‚Äù ‚ÄúBridesmaids‚Äù) as Ursula. ¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†
¬†
‚ÄúThe Little Mermaid‚Äù is directed by Oscar¬Æ nominee Rob Marshall (‚ÄúChicago,‚Äù ‚ÄúMary Poppins Returns‚Äù) with a screenplay by two-time Oscar nominee David Magee (‚ÄúLife of Pi,‚Äù ‚ÄúFinding Neverland‚Äù). The songs feature music from multiple Academy Award¬Æ winner Alan Menken (‚ÄúBeauty and the Beast,‚Äù ‚ÄúAladdin‚Äù) and lyrics by Howard Ashman, and new lyrics by three-time Tony Award¬Æ winner Lin-Manuel Miranda. The film is produced by two-time Emmy¬Æ winner Marc Platt (‚ÄúJesus Christ Superstar Live in Concert,‚Äù ‚ÄúGrease Live!‚Äù), Miranda, two-time Emmy winner John DeLuca (‚ÄúTony Bennett: An American Classic‚Äù), and Rob Marshall, with Jeffrey Silver (‚ÄúThe Lion King‚Äù) serving as executive producer.¬†

title: Origin of Life: You Can't Trust Everything You Hear (Long Story Short, Episode 9)
description:
Can you trust everything you hear about the origin of life? The short answer is ‚ÄúNo.‚Äù Many popular science expositors overstate the evidence for the natural, chemical origin of life and promote gross misinformation to the public on this topic. This video reviews popular claims made about the origin of life and shows why they are contradicted by the evidence, misleading, or flat out false.
 
This is the sixth of several episodes about the origin of life presented as part of the Long Story Short series. If you enjoyed this one, you will like all the others.
